title: Arizona - real GDP 2000 to 2018
yAxis: Real GDP in billion U.S. dollars
summary: In general Real GDP in billion U.S. dollars has rose over the Year.
Real GDP in billion U.S. dollars is roughly constant from 2012 to 2014, and finally slightly increasing from 2014 to 2018.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2017 and 2018.
The highest Real GDP in billion U.S. dollars, of value 309.07 was reached at Year 2018
Minimum Real GDP in billion U.S. dollars about 268.29 was reached at Year 2012
